title: For Sale:  Canik55 TP9 - titanium, DA/SA
postcontent:
I've decided to sell my rare titanium-finished version of the Canik55 TP9 Gen 1 after letting it live in my safe collecting dust. This Gen 1 version is built around the DA/SA trigger with the slide-mounted top decocker. This trigger is designed to be a little bit quirky; when you cock the striker by cycling the slide, it becomes a set trigger after cocking to engage single action mode. The double-action pull and single-action reset trigger are exactly as you'd expect.

Everything that I got from the original purchase is included in the sale. This means two 18-round magazines, the Serpa-style kydex holster with paddle and OWB attachments, replaceable backstrap, a magazine loader, an OEM wire cleaning brush, and of course the case which fits all of this together with Swiss Army knife efficiency.

I've taken it to the range 3 times, and put less than 200 rounds down the barrel.

If you want to hear way more about this gun than you need to, check out Nutnfancy's review on YouTube at (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=93-DJbuBUEA). Cliff notes? He loves it (there, I just saved you 41.3 minutes of your life) and raves about its unexpected quality.

Since I appear to be the only human on the internet selling a titanium one, I'm pricing it at $360 cash. If you are a TX CHL holder, I'll drop that down to $340 for my private sale peace-of-mind.

title: For Sale:  8mm Gew.88 Mauser / Steyr Collectors Rifle 1890
postcontent:
8mm Gew.88 Mauser / Steyr Collectors Rifle 1890


This one has history!

It’s a Steyr Gewehr 88 from 1890, way before WWI when the German Empire still had a Kaiser (emperor) and looks to be having used in the fight with the Ottoman Empire (Persia, now Iran). It is also often erroneously referred to as “Mauser” or “Mannlicher”.

It has all the hallmarks and markings that make this a rifle to have, from the Emperor’s crown to the Ottoman insignia.

Kaiser Wilhelm II was Germany’s last emperor and this baby could have seen action in Persia, then the 1st World War, on to WWII.

The bore’s rifling is still exceptional an the rifling twist is incredible, especially with this extra long barrel. Rounds chamber tight and the rifle works flawlessly, we shot 2 boxes and the accuracy is incredible! You can actually see those 8mm extra large bullets hit where they impact, even at a distance. Speaking of which, it has a flip up sight for long range shots. Whatever you hit with this baby, it’s going down hard…

With the sight in regular mode, it is sighted to 273 yards, then you can flip it up and it’s range is from 500 yards, with approx. 110 yard increments to a total range of 2187 yards.

5 shot clip, which can be strip loaded for fast reloading…

At 124 years of age this puppy will give most modern rifles a run for the money especially in accuracy, my buddy with his scoped rifle couldn’t believe the distances that this will hit at, without even a scope.

REAL German quality, even after a 124 years, it becomes very apparent when shooting it.

While you can just hang it on your wall as a show-off rife, it will be a real joy to shoot, take it hunting and show your buddies how it’s done Old School…

You WILL NOT run across another one like, it is very rare…

Cash or Postal Money Order
